# Visual Studio Code Usage

Visual Studio Code Usage Notes. #vscode #visual studio code

## Shortcuts

<!--Things that I always forget (>3) -->

* `Ctrl+U`: Open panel navigation
* `Ctrl+K, Z`: Zen Mode
* `Ctrl+K, O`
* `Ctrl+K+O`
* `Ctrl+Shift+V`: Markdown preview
* `Ctrl+K, V`: Markdown preview, side by side
* `Ctrl+Shift+O`: Markdown headers
* `F1`: Overall function search popup menu.
  * Same effect as `Ctrl+Shift+P`
* `Ctrl+P`: Quick open file in current workspace.
* `Alt+Left/Right`: Go to last edit locations (equivalent to `Ctrl+-` in visual studio); Use a 5-button mouse helps navigation significantly.

Note that VS Code do NOT have INSERT function, e.g. when editing ASCII tables.

## Extensions

* [Live Preview](https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=ms-vscode.live-server)

## Trick

* `F1-Simple Browser: Preview`
  * Reference: https://github.com/microsoft/vscode/pull/109276
* In console, hold Alt until cursor change to cross, now you can select blocks from console outputs and copy them!
